			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Most enchanters are familiar with the Innoruk's Sarcasim focus that lowers the agroo generated from casting Tash on a mob.  This effect can save and enchanter alot of grief on raids, or exp groups by allowing them to Tash earlier without getting agroo.
<br />

<br />
The down side of Innoruk's Sarcasim is that it isnt a very common focus and in many cases isnt available on gear that a raiding chanter would wear stat wise if they didnt need the focus.  (no one in my guild has the Anguish Gloves yet)
<br />

<br />
Examples:  Staff of Swiftness, Stone of Perfidious Wanting, Sharp Ended Lever?
<br />

<br />
But there is a way with the new Bandolier function to switch out your Innoruk's Sarcasim item when needed, and then switch back to your regular gear once Tash is done.  And heres how its done...
<br />

<br />
Open the Bandolier window and Create two profiles, one we will call "Tashicide" that has your Innoruks Sarcasim item Equiped.  The second we will call "Standard" this will have your stat items equiped.
<br />

<br />
Then make a hotkey for tash that looks like this
<br />

<br />
/Bandolier Activate Tashicide
<br />
/cast 6, /cast 6
<br />
/rsay TASH -- %T
<br />
/pause 4
<br />
/Bandolier Activate Standard
<br />

<br />
Now whenever you hit your trusty Tash button it switches in and out your Innoruks Sarcasim item for you.  I hope you all find this useful.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Psychoactive Effects</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by psychoactive on Wed Mar 02, 2005 10:54 am; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
