			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My old macro was:
<br />
/cast 2
<br />
/pause 10
<br />
%T has been TASHED
<br />

<br />
(10 pause gets the message immediately after the cast completes - 1 sec cast)
<br />

<br />
New macro (tested and had fun with last night)
<br />

<br />
/Bandolier Activate Tash
<br />
/cast 2
<br />
/pause 10
<br />
%T has been TASHED
<br />
/bandolier activate Normal
<br />

<br />
If you really want it to cast twice you can  do it like:
<br />

<br />
/bandolier activate Tash
<br />
/cast 2
<br />
/pause 10, /cast 2
<br />
%T has been TASHED
<br />
/bandolier activate Normal
<br />

<br />
I know the third line looks weird, but it takes affect as cast, cast, pause, you always put the pause first in a line, but it happens after what's second in macros.  And if you want a tiny pause between the two cast attempts put a /pause on the second line becure the /cast (it again goes off after).</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
